      "text": "Discussion: Evidence shows that pedestrians are not comfortable walking down long straight streets with endless “vanishing point” perspectives ahead. This experience seems to be disorienting as well as lacking in a sense of enclosure, which in turn is essential to make the street more attractive to pedestrians.¹ Drivers and riders in vehicles also benefit from the identification of wayfinding landmarks.",
