      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "One of the best ways to handle this need is to interrupt the street with one or more structures along its axis, creating “terminated vistas”. These can be buildings or parts of buildings, natural features, or other landmark elements. The streets can wind around the structures (as in the photo at the beginning of this pattern) or change angle, or simply terminate in a T-intersection.",
